Installing ChucK
---
To install the latest release, visit:
    https://chuck.stanford.edu/release/

(macOS and Windows), the installer will install two separate programs:
    miniAudicle (GUI-based IDE for ChucK)
    chuck (command line ChucK)

(Linux) build from source:
    https://chuck.stanford.edu/release/


Installing (command-line) ChucK using Homebrew
---
    brew install chuck


Building ChucK
---
To build the latest chuck from source code, either download the latest
source archive (https://chuck.stanford.edu/release/), or clone the chuck
repo from github.

Please README.md or https://github.com/ccrma/chuck for more details on
building ChucK from source.


Got questions?
---
Join us on any of the ChucK Community channels:
    https://chuck.stanford.edu/community/

Join the ChucK Community Discord:
    https://discord.gg/ENr3nurrx8
